🚗 Premier Vehicles

Premier Vehicles is a modern vehicle marketplace web application built with **Next.js 14 (App Router)**.
Users can browse bikes and cars, view detailed listings, and interact with sellers through chat and WhatsApp (authentication required).



📌 Project Overview

Premier Vehicles allows users to:

* Browse available vehicles
* View detailed product pages
* See image galleries using sliders
* Contact sellers
* Authenticate before chatting or reporting ads
* Experience a responsive and modern UI

The project follows a clean component-based architecture using modern frontend technologies.


🛠 Tech Stack

⚙️ Framework

 **Next.js 14** (App Router)
 React 18
 TypeScript

🎨 Styling & UI

Tailwind CSS
 ShadCN UI Components
 React Icons

📦 Libraries Used

 Swiper.js (Image Slider)
 React Hot Toast (Notifications)
 Context API (Authentication)
 Next.js Navigation (`useRouter`, `useParams`)

📁 Project Structure

app/
 ├── bikes/
 │    └── [id]/
 │         └── page.tsx
 ├── components/
 │    ├── common/
 │    ├── auth/
 │    └── Footer.tsx
 ├── context/
 │    └── AuthContext.tsx
 ├── data/
 │    └── Data.json



🚀 Features

🏍 Dynamic Vehicle Details Page

 Dynamic routing using `[id]`
 Data fetched from local JSON
 ID matching handled properly (string-based IDs like `bike-3`)
 Error toast if vehicle not found

🖼 Image Gallery

 Built using **Swiper.js**
 Autoplay enabled
 Thumbnail navigation
 Image counter display

🔐 Authentication System

 Context API based auth state
 Modal opens if user tries:

   Chat
   WhatsApp
   Report Ad
 Protected actions require login

📞 Contact Options

 Call Seller button
 WhatsApp integration
 Chat system (Auth protected)

📍 Product Information

 Title
 Price
 Location
 Year
 Speed
 Engine CC
 Power HP
 Description
 Vehicle Details Section

🔔 Notifications

 Error handling using React Hot Toast
 Example: “Bike Not Found”



🧠 Key Concepts Implemented

 Dynamic Routing (App Router)
 useParams Hook
 useRouter Navigation
 Conditional Rendering
 TypeScript Interfaces
 Component Reusability
 Authentication Guard Logic
 State Management with Context API



📊 Example Product Data Structure

json
{
  "id": "bike-3",
  "title": "YBR 125G",
  "price": "PKR 3.25 lacs",
  "city": "Peshawar, Saddar",
  "brand": "Honda",
  "model": "GT Edition",
  "year": 2019,
  "speed": 2000,
  "engineCC": 200,
  "powerHP": 20,
  "description": "Urgent need to sell...",
  "image": [
    "/images/yamaha-1.png",
    "/images/yamaha-2.png"
  ],
  "sold": false,
  "inSale": true
}




⚠️ Important Development Notes

 IDs are strings (e.g., `"bike-3"`)
 Dynamic route folder must be named `[id]`
 Consistent property naming (e.g., `model` not `Model`)
 Image array must not be empty

💻 Installation & Setup

1️⃣ Clone the Repository

bash
git clone https://github.com/your-username/premier-vehicles.git
```

### 2️⃣ Install Dependencies

bash
npm install


3️⃣ Run Development Server

bash
npm run dev


Visit:
http://localhost:3000

